										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>For those who can still get their congregations to add a service this week:</p>
<p>Here is the 1945 Minhat Todah- Service for Thanksgiving Day, Congregation Shearith Israel, NY by Rabbi David de Sola Pool.</p>
<p>Happy Holiday- Let me know if anyone uses it.</p>
<p><a href="https://kavvanah.files.wordpress.com/2009/11/thanksgiving-service-pool.pdf">Thanksgiving Service- 1945 Rabbi de Sola Pool</a> (pdf of full service)</p>
<p>There are several good sermons from Rabbi Leo Jung for Thanksgiving Sabbath and a couple of shiurim on the web from Rav Soloveitchik from the Wednesday on the eve of Thanksgiving.<a href="http://613.org/rav/notes1.html#American%20Jewish"> Here is one of my favorites from Nov. 22, 1975</a></p>
<p><strong>Update 2017 </strong></p>
<p>in 2016, I posted a <a href="https://kavvanah.wordpress.com/2016/11/15/service-for-thanksgiving-day-1905-in-commemoration-of-250-years-of-jews-in-the-us/">1905 service for the Sabbath before Thanksgiving written</a> by <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Henry_Pereira_Mendes">Rev H. Pereira Mendes </a>of the Spanish- Portuguese synagogue of NY</p>
<p>And in 2014, I posted the Thanksgiving service from <a href="https://kavvanah.wordpress.com/2014/11/22/service-for-thanksgiving-day-1940-rabbi-joseph-lookstein/">Kehilath Jeshurun 1940 and prayer from Rabbi Joseph Lookstein</a>.</p>
